    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/data-type-classification-schema-design/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "The paper focuses on Ion Identity Molecular Networking (IIMN) for LC-MS2 metabolomics data. While it mentions support for LC-MS data and briefly references MS-DIAL's capability to process 'various nontargeted LC-MS metabolomics experiments, including ion mobility mass spectrometry', the paper does not describe or implement a general data-type classification schema for routing LC, GC, IMS, and MS imaging to distinct processing pipelines. The paper's scope is narrowly focused on connecting ion species within LC-MS2 networks, not on designing a multi-instrument type-classification system.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-021-23953-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "data-type-classification-schema-design",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Design and implement a data-type classification schema that declares and categorizes mass spectrometry input types (LC, GC, IMS, MS imaging) to enable selective, type-aware processing module dispatch.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:04.019160+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/data-type-classification-schema-design/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To reach a broad user base, we interfaced the IIMN workflow with three widely used open source MS processing tools (MZmine17, MS-DIAL18, and XCMS13,16)... MS-DIAL34 is a polyvalent mass spectrometry data processing software capable of processing various nontargeted LC-MS metabolomics experiments, including ion mobility mass spectrometry",
      "asbval:note": "MZmine is confirmed as a tool integrated with IIMN for LC-MS data processing. However, the paper does not describe MZmine as implementing a general data-type classification schema or module dispatch routing for GC, IMS, and MS imaging. The paper only documents MZmine's role in the IIMN workflow for LC-MS2 data. MS-DIAL is noted to support ion mobility, but no evidence shows either tool implements the claimed type-classification schema for selective module dispatch across multiple instrument types.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-021-23953-9",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "data-type-classification-schema-design",
